    examTip: "CKD-MBD drug layers: (1) Phosphate binders: sevelamer (non-Ca²⁺), lanthanum, calcium acetate. (2) Active vitamin D: calcitriol, paricalcitol (selective VDR activator — less hypercalcemia), doxercalciferol. (3) Calcimimetic: cinacalcet/etelcalcetide (CaSR modulation). (4) Nutritional D: cholecalciferol/ergocalciferol. Target: PTH 2-9x upper normal for CKD 5, phosphorus <5.5, calcium normal. Avoid aluminum-based binders (encephalopathy, osteomalacia).",
